Hong Kong's trade surplus more than doubled to 5.09 billion Hong Kong dollars (US$651.6 million) in August from HK$2.27 billion a year earlier, according to government figures. 

The figure represents an improvement from July's surplus of HK$3.81 billion. 

For the year's first-eight months, Hong Kong's trade account showed a deficit of HK$4.57 billion compared with a shortfall of HK$6.77 billion a year earlier. 

Total August exports rose 15% to HK$53.05 billion from HK$46.1 billion a year earlier and were up 1% from HK$52.54 billion in July.
August imports totaled HK$47.97 billion, up 10% from HK$43.83 billion in August 1988, and fell 2% from July's HK$48.72 billion. 

For the first-eight months, total exports rose 22% to HK$368.74 billion from HK$303.15 billion a year ago.
Imports for the first-eight months rose 21% to HK$373.32 billion from HK$309.91 billion a year earlier. 

